definition: to have the right to/to be entitled to/to have authority/powerful
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
person in power/the one with authority/the guy in charge

sentences.english: Most importantly, this album has a stamp of Metallica written all over it.
sentences.chinese: 最重要的是，这张专辑的邮票金属书面所有权。

sentences.english: The lucky winner enjoys his choice of wives and lovers.
sentences.chinese: 幸运的优胜者可以有权选择不止一位妻子和爱人。

sentences.english: All rights to the Olympic symbol belong exclusively to the IOC.
sentences.chinese: 奥林匹克标志的所有权属国际奥委会专有。

sentences.english: We do not entertain buyer who do not pay in full!
sentences.chinese: 如果买主没付全款，本人有权不出货。

sentences.english: The centre reserves the right to cancel a programme if there is insufficient number of enrollments.
sentences.chinese: 如报读人数不足，本中心有权取消有关课程。

sentences.english: Looking back, it was collective code ownership at its finest!
sentences.chinese: 现在回想起来，集体性的代码所有权非常有用。

sentences.english: Party B shall still have the ownership of the equipment until Party B is paid in full.
sentences.chinese: 甲方未付清全款前，设备的所有权仍归乙方所有。

sentences.english: The issue remains that the other South-asian countries have the rights to claim these territories.
sentences.chinese: 南亚的其他国家也有权诉诸对南沙群岛的主权。

sentences.english: TCCC must have the right to verify the copy with the inspecting company.
sentences.chinese: TCCC公司有权与审核机构进行核实报告的真实性。

sentences.english: We have a right to know if a potential partner has herpes.
sentences.chinese: 我们有权知道潜在的伴侣是否患有疱疹。

sentences.english: This would be a valid passing opportunity regardless of whether there was pre-existing overlap.
sentences.chinese: 这时后车有权超越，无论有无预先存在“重叠”。

sentences.english: Propofol is normally administered only in hospital settings.
sentences.chinese: 一般说来，只有医院才有权开异丙酚。

sentences.english: Each door opens onto another country. We readers have unprecedented rights of access to complementary and contradictory worlds.
sentences.chinese: 作为读者，我们有权进入互不相同或完全对立的世界。

sentences.english: The ownership of the supplied material or parts remains with the foreign client.
sentences.chinese: 来料或来件的所有权仍属国外客户。

sentences.english: The Constitution must give citizens confidence that they will have control of their own destinies .
sentences.chinese: 宪法应给公民信心，他们有权掌握自己的命运。

sentences.english: the carrier against whom an action has been brought shall have the right to require the other carrier to join in the proceedings.
sentences.chinese: 被提起诉讼的承运人有权要求另一承运人参加应诉。

definition: to have no right/to have no authority
right (i.e. an entitlement to sth)/(classical) power and wealth
provision/to fix/to set/to formulate/to stipulate/to provide/regulation/rule/CL:個|个[ge4]
